"No bad?"

"No."

"Thank God for that. But come in. You must be weary, for you have had a long day."

"This is my friend, Dr. Watson. He has been of most vital use to me in several of my cases, and a
lucky chance has made it possible for me to bring him out and associate him with this
investigation."

"I am delighted to see you," said she, pressing my hand warmly. "You will, I am sure, forgive
anything that may be wanting in our arrangements, when you consider the blow which has come so
suddenly upon us."

"My dear madam," said I, "I am an old campaigner, and if I were not I can very well see that no
apology is needed. If I can be of any assistance, either to you or to my friend here, I shall be
indeed happy."